There are a few options for using the framework after cloning
1. remove .git dir and make a new project, new repository, etc - 
   this looses the framework history - normally an OK thing
2. after initial commit, clone --bare  
   cp bare repo to the git server
   update the config to point to the new remote repository, 
   pull from the remote to get it connected properly

Do not create a new branch of the framework repository and push it to the
ritcframework remote repository. Always make a new project/new remote repo 

1.  Two Options for submodule
	1. After clone and remove the git dir to create a new project
	   1. rm -Rf .git
       2. delete .gitmodule file
	   3. git init
	   4. git add .
	   5. git submodule add ssh://wer@www.wereveal.com/srv/git/ritclibrary
	2. After clone but use framework git history
	   1. git submodule init
	   2. git submodule update
2.  composer.phar update
3.  cd vendor/bin
4.  ./classmap_generator.php -l ../../app/src -w -o ../../app/config/autoload_classmap.php
5.  cd ../../
6.  git add .
7.  git commit -m "Initial Commit" (or whatever message you want)
8.  cd ../
9.  git clone --bare dir_name repo_name.git
10. cp bare repo to git server
11. cd repo
12. git pull (connects it)

Any time you want the latest version of the submodule(s) do git submodule update
Best practice, don't make modifications to the submodule, don't use git pull in the submodule

classmap_generator needs to be run anytime a new class file is added to the app.
